  "prompt": "What are the safety precautions on handling shotguns proposed by the NRA in the entire U.S. including it\u2019s territories and possessions? 2",
  "response": "The National Rifle Association (NRA) recommends the following comprehensive gun safety rules, known as the \"NRA Gun Safety Rules\":\n\n1. Always keep the gun pointed in a safe direction\n- Never point a firearm at anything you don't intend to shoot\n- Use common sense to ensure the firearm is pointed away from people\n\n2. Always keep your finger off the trigger until ready to shoot\n- Keep your finger outside the trigger guard and alongside the frame\n- Only place finger on trigger when you have made a conscious decision to fire\n\n3. Always treat every firearm as if it is loaded\n- Check the firearm's chamber and magazine to confirm unloaded status\n- Never assume a firearm is unloaded\n- Always handle firearms with the same caution as a loaded weapon\n\n4. Always be sure of your target and what is beyond it\n- Identify your target completely before shooting\n- Be aware of potential background and potential risks\n- Understand what might be behind or near your target\n\n5. Wear eye and ear protection\n- Use appropriate protective equipment during shooting\n- Protect hearing and vision from potential damage\n\n6. Use proper ammunition\n- Only use manufacturer-recommended ammunition\n- Ensure ammunition matches firearm specifications\n\nThese rules apply universally across the United States, including all territories and possessions.",
